[src:xla-compiler/basic-linear-algebra-subprograms] LAPACK is a higher level Linear Algebra library built upon BLAS.
[src:xla-compiler/basic-linear-algebra-subprograms] Like BLAS, a reference implementation exists, but many alternatives like libFlame and MKL exist.
[src:xla-compiler/basic-linear-algebra-subprograms] It provides generic linear algebra subprograms (GLAS).
[src:xla-compiler/basic-linear-algebra-subprograms] It can be built on a CBLAS implementation.
