[src:xla-compiler/compiler-optimization] Many optimizations listed in other sections also benefit with no special changes, such as register allocation.
[src:xla-compiler/compiler-optimization] GVN eliminates redundancy by constructing a value graph of the program, and then determining which values are computed by equivalent expressions.
