[src:xla-compiler/compiler-optimization] The most frequently used variables should be kept in processor registers for the fastest access.
[src:xla-compiler/compiler-optimization] To find which variables to put in registers, an interference-graph is created.
[src:xla-compiler/compiler-optimization] Each variable is a vertex and when two variables are used at the same time (have an intersecting liverange) they have an edge between them.
